    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-09T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-09T08:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/576: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-09T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 9, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 9—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. The London Naval Conference 1935 opened this morning at 10:30 and followed the
                    procedure outlined in the Embassy’s 581, November 21, 5 p.m. and 592, November
                    26, 6 p.m.<note n="99" xml:id="d151fn99">Neither printed.</note> Following
                    delivery of the opening speeches the Conference resolved itself into committee
                    of the whole called First Committee which will meet tomorrow morning at 10:30 at
                    Clifford House. Texts of speeches being forwarded by mail.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d151fn1">For texts of speeches, see The London Naval Conference,
                        1935, <hi rend="italic">Report of the Delegates of the United States</hi>,
                        p. 48; the text of the speech delivered by the Chairman of the American
                        delegation is also printed in telegram No. 373, November 30, 1935, 4 p.m.,
                        to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_281">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 281</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
